
---


@startuml

' Define the main classes
class Department {
    +String name
    +List<Room> rooms
}

class Room {
    +String number
    +List<Bed> beds
}

class Bed {
    +String id
    +Category category
}

class Category {
    +String type (e.g., RH, RNH, SF)
    +double pricePerMonth
    +List<Bed> beds
}

class Inhabitant {
    +String id
    +String name
    +Date registrationDate
    +List<Stay> stays
    +List<WaitingListEntry> waitingListEntries
}

class Stay {
    +Date startDate
    +Date endDate
    +Category category
    +Boolean isSuspended
    +Invoice invoice
}

class WaitingListEntry {
    +Inhabitant inhabitant
    +Category category
    +int position
    +Proposal proposal
}

class Proposal {
    +Date proposedDate
    +boolean accepted
    +Date responseDeadline
    +boolean isValid
    +Stay stay
}

class Invoice {
    +Date invoiceDate
    +double totalAmount
    +double paidAmount
    +double outstandingAmount
    +List<Payment> payments
    +Stay stay
}

class Payment {
    +Date paymentDate
    +double amount
    +boolean isRefund
    +CreditNote creditNote (if applicable)
}

' Relationships

Department "1" -- "0..*" Room : contains
Room "1" -- "0..*" Bed : has
Bed "1" -- "1" Category : belongs to
Inhabitant "1" -- "0..*" Stay : has
Stay "1" -- "1" Category : of type
Inhabitant "1" -- "0..*" WaitingListEntry : on
WaitingListEntry "1" -- "1" Proposal : has
Proposal "1" -- "1" Stay : for
Proposal "1" -- "1" WaitingListEntry : related to
Stay "1" -- "0..1" Invoice : generates
Invoice "1" -- "0..*" Payment : has
Payment "1" -- "0..1" CreditNote : may create

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Classes and Relationships

- **Department**: Contains multiple rooms.
- **Room**: Has multiple beds.
- **Bed**: Belongs to a specific category and can be assigned to an inhabitant.
- **Category**: Defines a type of stay (RH, RNH, SF) with a monthly price.
- **Inhabitant**: Can have multiple stays and may be on a waiting list for a specific category.
- **Stay**: Represents a period during which an inhabitant occupies a bed in a specific category. It can be suspended or ended.
- **WaitingListEntry**: Tracks an inhabitant’s position in the waiting list for a specific category.
- **Proposal**: A suggestion made to an inhabitant to accept a bed in a specific category.
- **Invoice**: Generated monthly for each stay, tracking amounts paid and outstanding balances.
- **Payment**: Records when a payment is made toward an invoice.
- **CreditNote**: Created if a payment exceeds the invoice amount.

---

### 🧠 Notes

- The system supports **multiple stays** for an inhabitant, including **suspended stays**.
- The **waiting list** is sorted by **registration date**.
- **Invoices are generated monthly**, and can be modified until they are marked as **paid**.
- **Discounts apply** when an inhabitant has multiple active stays (e.g., service flat while in rest & nursing).
- **Payments** are tracked, and **credit notes** are issued for overpayments.

